Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from fraudsters who are replacing bank phone numbers has increased.
This is reported by "Kommersant" with reference to data from the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator provided the operators with information on more than 2,500 numbers that called customers of various financial institutions.
Operators have detected 189 cases of a number change.
Another 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases, restrictions were placed on the use of financial services.
Deputy head of the Central Bank's information security department, Artem Sychev, said that a wide range of Russian banks had encountered the change of number.
He explained that operators do not always respond to the Central Bank's warnings about fraudulent calls, citing the absence of such an obligation in the Law "On Communication".
Otkritie Bank, Rosbank and Alfa Bank confirmed the increase in fraudulent calls with a change of number.
As reported in the press service of "BiLayn", part of the information about fraudulent calls that the Central Bank transmitted was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are actually used by banks to communicate with customers.
Blocking them would have disrupted the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of fraudsters' numbers, which the operator will refer to each call to verify the number.
He explained that to create such a base, it would require amendments to the legislation.
