Regions invited to share secrets of business support
As it became known to the Parliamentary Gazette, on September 27, the Chairman of the Federation Council Committee on Economic Policy Andrei Kutupov sent a letter to the Minister of Economic Development Maxim Oreshkin and the Minister of Finance Anton Siluanov with a proposal to express their position on the initiatives of the subjects of the Federation to improve legislation in the field of support for small and medium enterprises (SMEs).
It 's time to establish interregional ties
The Federation Council Committee on Economic Policy summarized the information received from the regions on the programs for business development and the legalization of self-employment, as well as the results of such programs.
In their letters, the regions told the senators about the problems of SME development and sent proposals for improving the current legislation.
"Today, communication between regions is not sufficiently established, as a result of which the business community in all regions of the visit by the senators was indicated the lack of information about regional programs for the development of entrepreneurship in the country as a whole", - said Andrei Kutepov.
In the annex to the letter, which was sent to the Government, he presented a set of positive developments of the regions on the legalization of self-employment and summary data from the regions with proposals and problems (available in the editorial).
In addition to the relevant ministries, regional executive heads also receive the regional summary data.
The exchange of information on the success of the regions could give an impetus to the development of entrepreneurship as a whole.
The first step to this exchange would be to send the information that the Committee on Economic Policy has", the senator told the Parliamentary Gazette.
A useful experience
Today, many regions of the country have adopted and successfully operate support programmes for small and medium-sized businesses.
For example, in the Vologda region, the Entrepreneurship Support Center operates, which, in addition to financial support measures, assists businessmen in the certification of finished products.
In the Ivanovo region, a system of support for business has been developed, which provides for the implementation of the principle of one window through multifunctional centers.
In the Krasnodar Territory, grants are provided to start-up agricultural consumer cooperatives from the regional budget.
The centre for cluster development is located in the Orel region.
The Amur region within the framework of the federal project "Acceleration of small and medium-sized enterprises" provides for the possibility of subsidizing business incubators created on the basis of existing non-governmental coworking centers, at the expense of the federal budget.
In some other regions, special measures are being taken to support youth entrepreneurship.
Self-employed people continue to be taken out of the shadows
According to the regional authorities, a number of changes should be made to the existing legislation to support small and medium-sized businesses more effectively.
For example, Arkhangelsk region proposed to replace the term "self-employment" with "entrepreneurial activity", as it "best corresponds to the content of the state service to promote self-employment of unemployed citizens".
In the Ivanovo region, it is considered necessary to make amendments that provide for the expansion of the list of activities performed by self-employed citizens, including the types of activities for decorating and repairing residential premises, cottage buildings, conducting physical training.
The Bryansk region considers it important to increase the control of unscrupulous dairy producers with the help of the veterinary system "Mercury".
In the Kostroma and Magadan regions, the concept of "social entrepreneurship" and the areas of support for social entrepreneurship are advocated in the normative-legal field.
All the proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programmes to support small and medium-sized enterprises, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific draft laws.
"All the proposals from the regions will be taken into account when preparing state programs to support small and medium-sized businesses, and the most important ones will be developed in the form of specific law projects", - assured Andrey Kutepov.
The airline has helped passengers avoid the neighborhood of crying babies .
Japan Airlines (JAL) has launched a new feature: When booking seats on a plane, you can now see where young children will be seated.
Now, if you want to avoid being next to them.
Passengers on Japan Airlines (JAL) have been given the opportunity to take advantage of a new option to avoid unwanted proximity to small children.
The airline has launched a feature that allows you to track which seats your children will be sitting in.
When selecting seats in the cabin during ticket booking, passengers will be able to see the image of the child's head in the seats occupied by children aged eight days to two years.
Thus, those who do not want to fly near the babies because of the possible inconvenience associated with their crying may be able to get as far away from them as possible.
