One user complained that he was flying from New York to Doha a few weeks ago, and there were three crying children sitting next to him.
Another commenter suggested "adults only flights", saying they would be willing to pay extra for such a flight.
Many travelers have said they will now always choose Japan Airlines for their travels, as they see no comfort in flying next to a crying baby in an enclosed space.
